{"lemma":"كَفَرَة","slug":"كَفَرَة","root":"ك.ف.ر","root_slug":"ك-ف-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ك-ف-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"كافِر","root":"كفر","pos":"N","occurrence_count":156},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n37097","n37105"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%83%D9%8E%D9%81%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%A9"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"active participle of كَفَرَ (kafara)","tags":["active","form-of","participle"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"farmer","tags":["obsolete"],"examples":[{"text":"كَمَثَلِ غَيْثٍ أَعْجَبَ الْكُفَّارَ نَبَاتُهُ ثُمَّ يَهِيجُ فَتَرَاهُ مُصْفَرًّا ثُمَّ يَكُونُ حُطَامًا","english":"Like the example of a rain whose [resulting] plant growth pleases the farmers; then it dries and you see it turned yellow; then it becomes [scattered] debris"}]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"disbeliever, unbeliever"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"disbeliever, infidel","tags":["slur"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"ingrate, ungrateful","examples":[{"text":"قَالَ أَلَمْ نُرَبِّكَ فِينَا وَلِيدًا وَلَبِثْتَ فِينَا مِنْ عُمُرِكَ سِنِينَ (18) وَفَعَلْتَ فَعْلَتَكَ الَّتِي فَعَلْتَ وَأَنتَ مِنَ الْكَافِرِينَ (19)","english":"(18) He said “Did we not rear thee among us as a child? And thou didst dwell many years of thy life among us, (19) and thou didst that thy deed which thou didst, and thou wast one of the ingrates.”"}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Active participle of the verb كَفَرَ (kafara, “to disbelieve; to cover; to conceal”) from the root ك ف ر (k f r)."},"ipa":["/kaː.fir/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n37097","headword_ar":"كفّرهُ","root":"kfr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"takofiyrN","text_ar":"تَكْفِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 1, first signification, in three places.       -A2-  Hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaf~ara Al*~anoba","text_ar":"كَفَّرَ الذَّنْبَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(war in the cause of God [or the like])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"covered,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"concealed, the crime"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sin:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) (or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"expiated it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"annulled it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tkfyr","text_ar":"تكفير"},{"kind":"text","text":"with respect to acts of disobedience is like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iHobaATN","text_ar":"اـِحْبَاطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"with respect to reward. (S, K.) The saying in the Kur [v. 70.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lakaf~aronaA Eanohumo say~iy^aAtihimo","text_ar":"لَكَفَّرْنَا عَنْهُمْ سَيِّيَاتِهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"We would cover,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conceal, their sins, so that they should become as though they had not been:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or it may mean,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"We would do away with their sins;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as is indicated by another saying in the Kur [xi. 116,] “ good actions do away with sins. ” (El-Basáïr.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaf~ara A@ll~`hu Eanohu Al*~anoba","text_ar":"كَفَّرَ ا@للّٰهُ عَنْهُ الذَّنْبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God effaced his sin."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaf~ara Eano yamiynihi","text_ar":"كَفَّرَ عَنْ يَمِينِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He expiated his oath;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he performed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gave,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaf~aArap","text_ar":"كَفَّارَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a fast,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"alms, for the expiation of his oath"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Msb, K:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"takofiyrN","text_ar":"تَكْفِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"of an oath is the doing what is incumbent, or obligatory, for the violation, or breaking, thereof: (S:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaf~ara yamiynahu","text_ar":"كَفَّرَ يَمِينَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a vulgar phrase. (Mgh.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaf~arahu","text_ar":"كَفَّرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akofarahu","text_ar":"اَكْفَرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 4.       -A4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaf~ara lahu","text_ar":"كَفَّرَ لَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"takofiyrN","text_ar":"تَكْفِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, Mgh, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He did"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2621},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"obeisance to him, lowering his head,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bowing, and bending himself, and putting his hand upon his breast:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"put his hand upon his breast and bent himself down to him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he made a sign of humbling himself to him; did obeisance to him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) namely, an"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eiloj","text_ar":"عِلْج"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or unbeliever of the Persians or other foreigners] (A, Mgh) or a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*im~iY~","text_ar":"ذِمِّىّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or free non- Muslim subject of a Muslim government, i. e., a Christian, a Jew, or a Sabian] (Mgh) to the king; (A, Mgh;) or a slave to his master, or to his"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dihoqaAn","text_ar":"دِهْقَان"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or chief]: (TA:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kafara","text_ar":"كَفَرَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", [aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", accord. to the rule of of the K,] (TK,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaforN","text_ar":"كَفْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a Persian,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faArisiY~N","text_ar":"فَارِسِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", K, and so in the L and other lexicons, but in the TS"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAris","text_ar":"فَارِس"},{"kind":"text","text":", without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is probably a mistake of copyists, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"paid honour"},{"kind":"text","text":"to his king, (K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by making a sing with his head, near to prostration:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"takofiyrN","text_ar":"تَكْفِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a man's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"humbling himself"},{"kind":"text","text":"to another, (S, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bending himself, and lowering his head, nearly in the manner termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rukuwEN","text_ar":"رُكُوعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":";"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as one does when he desires to pay honour to his friend;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eiloj","text_ar":"عِلْج"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"does to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dihoqaAn","text_ar":"دِهْقَان"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tkfyr","text_ar":"تكفير"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the people of the scriptures [or Christians and Jews, and Sabians] one's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lowering his head"},{"kind":"text","text":"to his friend, like the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tasoliym","text_ar":"تَسْلِيم"},{"kind":"text","text":"with the Muslims: or one's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"putting his hand,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his two hands, upon his breast:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tkfyr","text_ar":"تكفير"},{"kind":"text","text":"in prayer is the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bending one's self much in the state of standing, before the action termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rukuwEN","text_ar":"رُكُوعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; the doing of which was disapproved by Mohammad, accord. to a trad. (TA.) It is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_i*aA A^aSobaHa","text_ar":"اـِذَا اَصْبَحَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@bonu A=dama faA_in~a AlA^aEoDaA='a tukaf~iru kul~uhaA lil~isaAni","text_ar":"ا@بْنُ ا=دَمَ فَاـِنَّ الاَعْضَا=ءَ تُكَفِّرُ كُلُّهَا لِلِّسَانِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"When the son of Adam rises in the morning, verily all the members abase themselves to the tongue,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and confess obedience to it, and humbly submit to its command."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"takofiyrN","text_ar":"تَكْفِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"crowning"},{"kind":"text","text":"a king"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with a crown,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[because] when he, or it, is seen, obeisance is done to him ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_i*aA ruy^iYa kuf~ira lahu","text_ar":"اـِذَا رُيِىَ كُفِّرَ لَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"). (K.) ―         -b3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"takofiyrN","text_ar":"تَكْفِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"below."}],"source_refs":["Mgh","Msb","K","S","A","TA","TK"]},{"entry_id":"n37105","headword_ar":"كَفْرَةٌ","root":"kfr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAfirN","text_ar":"كَافِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}